## Implementation Phases

### Phase 1 — Foundation & Data Layer
1. Configure `AuroraFeedFlowApp.swift`: inject `PersistenceController`, `AppEnvironment`, and `ThemeManager` as `@StateObject`/`@Environment` values; wire CloudKit container ID.
2. Define `AppEnvironment.swift` as the global `ObservableObject` holding references to all services (FeedStore, SyncEngine, SearchEngine, ThemeManager, UserPreferences).
3. Define CoreData model `AuroraFeedFlow.xcdatamodeld` with entities:
   - `CDFeed` (id, title, url, faviconURL, unreadCount, lastRefreshed, folderID, sortOrder)
   - `CDFeedItem` (id, feedID, title, url, author, publishedAt, summary, imageURL, isRead, isBookmarked, readingProgress)
   - `CDFolder` (id, name, sortOrder)
   - `CDCustomMenu` (id, name, iconName, colorHex, filterJSON, sortOrder)
   - All entities use `NSPersistentCloudKitContainer` for iCloud sync.
4. Implement `PersistenceController.swift` with `NSPersistentCloudKitContainer`, `.automaticallyMergesChangesFromParent = true`, `mergePolicy = NSMergeByPropertyObjectTrumpMergePolicy`, background context for writes.
5. Generate `CDFeed+CoreDataClass`, `CDFeedItem+CoreDataClass`, etc. with value-type bridging structs (`Feed`, `FeedItem`).

### Phase 2 — Networking & Feed Parsing
6. `NetworkClient.swift`: `async/await` URLSession wrapper, ETag/Last-Modified caching headers, configurable timeout, reachability guard.
7. `NetworkReachability.swift`: `NWPathMonitor` published via Combine, offline mode flag.
8. `FeedParserEngine.swift`: detects feed type (RSS/Atom/JSON) from `Content-Type` and XML root element; dispatches to specialized parser; returns `[FeedItem]`.
9. `RSSParser.swift`: `XMLParserDelegate`-based, handles RSS 2.0, MediaRSS extensions.
10. `AtomParser.swift`: Atom 1.0 parser.
11. `JSONFeedParser.swift`: `Codable` JSON Feed 1.1 struct decoder.
12. `OPMLParser.swift`: import/export OPML 2.0; generates `[Feed]` from outline elements.
13. `ImageLoader.swift`: progressive image loading with `NSCache` + disk cache via `FileManager`.

### Phase 3 — Theme System
14. `ColorPalette.swift`: semantic color tokens (background, surface, primary, secondary, accent, separator, unreadIndicator) for light/dark/system. Palette inspired by FEEED's warm whites, slate grays, ink blacks.
15. `Typography.swift`: font scale (headline, subheadline, body, caption, serif reader font), line height multipliers, dynamic type support.
16. `ThemeManager.swift`: `@Observable`, persists theme choice, font family, font size, density; publishes changes.
17. `AnimationConstants.swift`: spring constants (stiffness, damping), easing curves for cards, pull-to-dismiss, sidebar expand.

### Phase 4 — Core Data Services
18. `SearchEngine.swift`: `NSFetchRequest` with `NSPredicate` for title/author/description; `FuzzyMatcher` for scoring partial matches; publishes sorted results reactively.
19. `BackgroundRefreshScheduler.swift`: register `BGAppRefreshTask`, schedule periodic refresh, invoke `FeedParserEngine` per feed, write to background CoreData context.
20. `ChangeTracker.swift`: Combine `debounce(1.5s)` pipeline that coalesces read/unread/bookmark mutations before persisting — reduces CloudKit write rate.

### Phase 5 — iCloud Sync
21. `CloudKitSyncEngine.swift`: monitors `NSPersistentCloudKitContainer` import/export notifications; exposes sync state stream; triggers push notification subscription.
22. `SyncConflictResolver.swift`: conflict policy — server wins for read/unread status; merge (union) for bookmarks; server wins for feed list. Writes resolved objects back to context.
23. `SyncStatusMonitor.swift`: publishes `SyncStatus` enum (idle, syncing, error(String), lastSyncedAt) consumed by sync indicator in Settings.
24. Handoff: implement `NSUserActivity` with `activityType = "com.aurora.readArticle"` carrying `articleURL` and `readingProgress`; `onContinueUserActivity` handler in `AuroraFeedFlowApp`.

### Phase 6 — Sidebar & Navigation
25. `AppCoordinator.swift`: `NavigationSplitView` root; sidebar → feed list → article reader. On iPad: three-column; on iPhone: navigation stack.
26. `SidebarView.swift`: sections — All Feeds, Unread, Bookmarks, Trending; custom menus list (drag-to-reorder with `.onMove`); folder hierarchy with expand animation.
27. `SidebarMenuRow.swift`: SF Symbol icon + custom color swatch + badge count; long-press context menu for edit/delete.

### Phase 7 — Feed List & Article Reader
28. `FeedListView.swift`: `LazyVStack` of `FeedCard`; section headers by recency (Today, Yesterday, This Week, Earlier); pull-to-refresh; swipe-to-mark-read; swipe-to-bookmark.
29. `FeedCard.swift`: thumbnail (ProgressiveImageView), title (2-line truncated, headline font), feed name, time ago, unread indicator dot; card shadow via `CardShadowModifier`.
30. `FeedListViewModel.swift`: Combine pipeline from CoreData `@FetchRequest` filtered by selected menu; maps to `[FeedItem]`; triggers refresh on appear.
31. `ArticleReaderView.swift`: full-screen sheet with spring pull-to-dismiss (`DragGesture`); large serif title, metadata row, body text via `AttributedString` rendered in `Text` (native) or `WKWebView` for HTML articles; reading progress tracker.
32. `ArticleWebView.swift`: `WKWebView` wrapped in `UIViewRepresentable`; injected CSS matching app typography; blocks external trackers.
33. `ReaderToolbar.swift`: bookmark toggle, share sheet, open-in-safari, font size slider, text width toggle.

### Phase 8 — Custom Menu Builder
34. `MenuBuilderView.swift`: list of saved menus + "New Menu" button; drag-to-reorder (`.onMove`).
35. `FilterEditorView.swift`: compose filters — feed selector, tag/category picker, date range (last 24h/week/all), read status toggle, minimum word count (long reads); previews matching count live.
36. `MenuBuilderViewModel.swift`: builds `filterJSON` predicate string; validates; saves `CDCustomMenu`.
37. `IconColorPicker.swift`: SF Symbol search grid + color wheel; outputs (iconName, colorHex) pair.

### Phase 9 — Settings
38. `SettingsView.swift`: grouped form — Reading, Appearance, Refresh, Sync, Data, About.
39. `FontSettingsView.swift`: font family picker (System, New York, Palatino, Georgia), size stepper, line height slider, preview card.
40. `SyncSettingsView.swift`: sync status indicator (animated pulse when syncing), last synced timestamp, "Sync Now" button, iCloud account status.

### Phase 10 — OPML, Bookmarks, Search UI
41. `OPMLImportView.swift`: `fileImporter` document picker for `.opml`; parse → preview feed list → confirm import.
42. `OPMLExportView.swift`: generates OPML XML from `[CDFeed]`; `shareLink` to export.
43. `BookmarksView.swift`: same card layout as feed list, filtered to `isBookmarked == true`; supports swipe-to-unbookmark.
44. Global search: `NavigationSplitView` toolbar `.searchable(text:)` binding to `SearchEngine`; real-time results grouped by Feeds / Articles / Authors.

### Phase 11 — iPad & Platform Polish
45. `NavigationSplitView` with `.balanced` column width, always-visible sidebar on iPad landscape.
46. Keyboard shortcuts: `⌘R` refresh, `⌘F` search, `⌘B` bookmark, `⌘[`/`⌘]` navigate articles, `⌘,` settings.
47. Drag-and-drop: feeds draggable between folders (`onDrag`/`onDrop` with `NSItemProvider`).
48. Stage Manager: `UIWindowScene` adaptive sizing, no hardcoded frame assumptions.
49. Pencil: `PencilKit` canvas overlay on article for annotations (optional enhancement).

### Phase 12 — Animations & Transitions
50. Card appear: staggered `withAnimation(.spring(response:0.4, dampingFraction:0.7))` with delay per index.
51. Pull-to-dismiss article: `DragGesture` → scale + opacity transition, spring return on cancel.
52. Sidebar row expand: `withAnimation(.easeInOut(duration:0.25))` height transition.
53. Unread badge: `.contentTransition(.numericText())` for count changes.
54. Loading skeleton: `redacted(reason:.placeholder)` shimmer via `TimelineView`.

### Phase 13 — Tests
55. `FeedParserTests`: mock RSS/Atom/JSON feed strings → assert correct `FeedItem` fields, date parsing, empty feed handling.
56. `SyncLogicTests`: mock `NSManagedObjectContext` → conflict resolution scenarios → assert expected merged state.
57. `ViewModelTests`: `FeedListViewModel` with in-memory CoreData store → publish changes → assert `@Published` outputs via `XCTestExpectation`.
58. `DatabaseIndexingTests`: insert 1000 items → measure `NSFetchRequest` execution time for search predicate < 100ms.

### Phase 14 — Optional Enhancements (AI Features)
59. AI Summaries: on-device `NaturalLanguage` framework extractive summarization; optional OpenAI API call for abstractive summary.
60. Topic Clustering: `MLKit` or `CoreML` text embedding → k-means via `Accelerate`; surface as "Related" section in reader.
61. Recommended Feeds: collaborative filtering based on read history stored locally.
62. Feed Health Monitor: track HTTP status per feed URL over refresh history; alert on repeated 404/403.

