## Verification Steps

1. Build with `xcodebuild -scheme AuroraFeedFlow -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 16 Pro'` — zero errors.
2. Add a real RSS URL (e.g. `https://feeds.feedburner.com/TechCrunch`) — feed parses and items appear in list.
3. Mark item as read on iPhone simulator → kill app → relaunch → item remains read.
4. Enable iCloud in simulator → verify `NSPersistentCloudKitContainer` syncs to second simulator.
5. Run XCTest suite — all tests pass, search benchmark < 100ms for 1000 items.
6. iPad split view: sidebar always visible in landscape, collapses in portrait.
7. Pull-to-dismiss article sheet: spring animation plays correctly, returns on cancel.
8. Custom menu with "Unread + last 24h" filter → correct items shown.
9. OPML import test with sample file (BBC, Guardian feeds) → feeds added.
10. Background refresh: send BGAppRefreshTask via device log → new items appear.

