## Decisions
- CloudKit via `NSPersistentCloudKitContainer` (not manual CKRecord) — reduces boilerplate, handles conflict notifications natively.
- No third-party dependencies — pure Apple frameworks only (URLSession, XMLParser, CoreData, CloudKit, NaturalLanguage, BackgroundTasks, WebKit).
- Swift 6 strict concurrency — all CoreData work on dedicated actor, UI on MainActor.
- `@Observable` macro (iOS 17+) for ViewModels; `@FetchRequest` in views requiring live CoreData updates.
- Minimum deployment target: iOS 17.0 / iPadOS 17.0.
- Article rendering: native `AttributedString` in `Text` for plain-text content; `WKWebView` with injected CSS for HTML articles.
- Offline mode: `NetworkReachability` gates all network calls; reads always served from CoreData.
